==Korean==

===Hanja===
{{ko-hanja|hangeul=욕|eumhun=|rv=yok|mr=yok|y=yok}}

The syllable 욕 can have different meanings depending on context.

욕, when derived from the hanja 辱, carries the meaning of shame, disgrace, or humiliation in English.

This is the sense used in Sino‑Korean vocabulary such as 굴욕 (屈辱) “humiliation.”

